<br>
first, the way the archer is standing makes no sense.  I know it looks better, but if you are using a bow and arrow, you have to hold a correct stance, look into hunting/ archery books for that sort of thing.<br>
<br>
Second, the dwarf is being knocked back, right?  If so, try to make him look less stiff.  If he's not finished (dead) yet, try to make it seem like it, have him keeping his head from hitting the ground, trying not to land in any uncomfortable way.  If he IS done, make him look a little more rag dollish.<br>
<br>
Third, The fighter's stance is weird.  he is apparently in midair, so you may want to make his bending leg bend a lot more and make the straight leg straighter, kind of like he's putting his all into lunging at the thing.  And since he seems to already be near enough to the treant to hit it, have him either bringing his sword down or already hitting the treant.<br>
<br>
and this is just a trick i've picked up, when doing stick figures for a scene, make weapons more like lines as well, forget the details, the weapons are far less important than the character's poses at this point.<br>
<br>
i hope this helped and wasn't too critical -_-;; <p>&quot;General rule: You can surf on anything!&quot;<br>
